Hi Anand,

You should save your model in the train.py script instead of the notebook, like this:

 os.makedirs('outputs', exist_ok=True)
 joblib.dump(value=model, filename='outputs/model.pkl')
After this once you get the best model from,

best_run = hyperdrive_run.get_best_run_by_primary_metric()
then you can register that model using the model saved by train.py script like this,

model = best_run.register_model(model_name='hyperdrive_model', model_path='./outputs/model.pkl',
                       model_framework=Model.Framework.SCIKITLEARN,
                       model_framework_version='0.19.1')
